description:
Deep sea divers, deadly supernatural hell-hounds, loved-up aliens and lashings of wondrous carnage and mayhem!

Featuring strips by Mark Bertolini (Markosia, FUBAR Press), David Hailwood (Toxic, Strip Magazine), Tony Suleri (Scar Comics, Futurequake) and many more!

It's Take-Your-Cyborg-Assassin-with-Amnesia-to-School Day! As George tries to help Angelica blend in, and prays no sign of her murderous personality emerges, cracks begin to emerge that even she doesn't understand. Meanwhile, federal agents are closing in on their missing prototype, and a local cop begins to suspect the link between Angelica and his partner's death. All this and the truth behind Angelica's tinkering with George's spinal column! The bizarre, hilarious, and riveting story continues.

The Bad Dreams' quest to restore Night continues as Mary and her companions find themselves face to face with Amorpha, the Queen of Dreams. Under her spell, nothing is truly as it seems. The plot thickens as secrets are revealed and new ones take their place!

Note: The digital edition (6/18/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
In the midst of a night of drunken debauchery, Brown, an uncouth ruffian-for-hire, is approached by the mysterious Mr. Orlack — who offers the thug a job most lucrative... and even more distasteful.
name: To Your Health, Part One

description:
As their story continues, Kei and Atsushi still have not come to terms with their deep attraction to each other. Outside circumstances continue to threaten what they have. In the end, will Kei and Atsushi face their fears and abandon their pride? Will they finally succumb to temptation? Through it all, one thing is certain - despite threats made by those who want to hurt them, despite the harm they inflict upon themselves, Kei and Atsushi will protect each other fiercely in hopes of conquering tomorrow.

Chapter Titles

  • Act.4 3/3
  • The Boys with Tomorrow
  • My Caged Beast
  • INDIGO BLUE
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: The Boys With Tomorrow To Conquer

description:
Road Rage

Trapped in the War Zone. No back-up. Surrounded by powerful villains eager to get a crack at him, Mith must fight to protect and free a victim. He's on their turf now. Getting in was the easy part. Getting out... Bet the sessions with Doctor Torment don't seem so bad now!
name: Road Rage

description:
Tick Tock IPA is a continuation of the Clockwork Watch story, it pre-dates our second book "Breakaway", and is about the liberation of Clockworks from servitude. It has certain parallels with the abolition of slavery or the fight for civil rights. Clockwork Servants finally get a voice in Tick Tock IPA, when Ervin accidentally breaks free from his programming.

A foreword by author Robert Rankin helps to set the scene, and gives an insight into the world of Clockwork Watch, and background to this project.
name: Tick Tock IPA

description:
It's 1969, and the eyes of the whole world are focused on the moon, where the Apollo 11 mission is about to make one giant leap for mousekind. But the time-traveling Pirate Cats are on the scene and they want to sabotage this historic moment with their most audacious and harebrained plan ever. To stop them, Geronimo and his cousin Trap will have to get to the moon first. Fasten your seat belts: a rat-tastic space race is underway!

Note: The digital edition (6/18/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: The First Mouse on the Moon

description: Dr. Lucy Chaplin is brilliant, sexy, and wealthy. But when a mysterious figure from Lucy's past physically transforms her and several other Solar City women, a race against the clock begins. "Halloween Man: Eye of the Beholder" is an all-new story line dealing with the topic of body image within the superhero genre. Written by series creator Drew Edwards, with art by Sergio Calvet (Magic of Myths, Dark of the Forest.) Also, this issue features two stories of romance gone wrong pulled from "Halloween Man's web comic" past!
name: Eye of the Beholder

description:
Take some time for an adventure to a magical world with two cute bunnies... two foul, drug using, butt-naked bunnies that go on adorably offensive, and insultingly hilarious adventures!!

Having defeated the un-caring bears, the bunnies meet Drug Mule Doug and more outrageous characters on their quest to sell drugs... er, save Christmas!

volume.name: Itty Bitty Bunnies in Rainbow Pixie Candy Land

description: America's sweetheart, Audrey Hepburn, makes an appearance in one of Burma's lives! Burma tells the tale of how he clawed his way onto the set of Breakfast at Tiffany's, while his associates make quick work of his enemies—all except one, that is. The fascinating story by writer Paul Tobin (Bandette, Colder) and artist Benjamin Dewey (The Tragedy Series) continues!
name: Chapter Three

description: In 1999, after a reign of terror that claimed the lives of eight female victims, the trail for "The Cleaner" killer ran cold. Like the Jack "The Ripper" Case, The Black Dahlia and The Zodiac Killer, it has been a question contemplated with every unsolved murder for the last 100 years. Why would a killer with such an immense lust for blood, stop killing? Maybe his final victim holds the key.
name: Predation

description: A prison breakout and a crime spree through Tokyo... what better way to rekindle a childhood friendship? But Naja's sentimentality takes a backseat to her agenda for revenge...

See the Sin like you've never seen before in this digital exclusive edition complete with inked pages, sketches and a variant cover gallery! One hero goes rogue. Another loses his head. Dr. Strange and the Punisher team up for a daring raid, and all trails now lead to one suspect. But he... how is that even possible?
name: Secret Warriors

description:
Black Market Baby

Frank steps away from the computer. His first adventure in the real world, without Quinn and the team, might also be his last.
name: Black Market Baby

description: Rumor 3: Now, at last, we finally hear Hikaru's side of the story. Hilarity ensues!
name: Rumor 3

volume.name: Princess Ai: Rumors From the Other Side

description: As preparations for Aldair's arranged marriage commences, she rebels as all of cView is turned upside down when the OccupEye system unexpectedly goes off-line. The eye-popping sci-fi series, Bloody Disgusting calls, "beautiful, imaginative, and thought provoking" continues!

TO EVEN MORE WORSE! In the belly of the beast, Tom and his crew are about to learn just what kind of space pirate they're dealing with, as Tom makes things even worse than they were before. If you're ever in space and you meet a group of space pirates, don't flirt with, or try to sleep with, any space pirate's daughter. Got it?
name: Danger in Deep Space Part 3

description: Damon’s fears about the reemergence of Stefan’s ripper side returning seem to be bearing true. Will his brother’s comrades in the African desert survive the battle only to fall to a fellow soldier?
name: War Effort Part 2 of 2

description: He has to go back! Now home on Earth, Deron must work with an unexpected ally to return to the alien planet and rescue Cody. Zorg isn't waiting around, though, and has his own ideas for saving his king.

The New York Times bestselling novel now adapted into comics, featuring full-color illustrations by Hugo Award-nominated artist Jimmy Broxton, and as adapted by fan-favorite writers Jimmy Palmiotti and Justin Gray. This contemporary dystopian classic--hailed by Justin Cronin, New York Times bestselling author of The Passage, as "an epic feat of imagination"--will captivate readers both familiar and new. This is the story of mankind clawing for survival, of mankind on the edge. The world outside has grown unkind, the view of it limited, talk of it forbidden. But there are always those who hope, who dream. These are the dangerous people, the residents who infect others with their optimism. Their punishment is simple. They are given the very thing they profess to want: They are allowed outside.

In issue #2 of 6: She's the new sheriff in town. But she doesn't know the laws have changed, or that she's out of luck. .

The zombified 16-bit console memory card has lain dormant in a thrift store bargain bin for a year now, with its horrible curse a long-lost save game. Meanwhile, a new 32-bit console has been released! Its denizens start to enjoy the benefits of "full-motion video" and "blaster processing", when the new memory card burns out. The system can take older cards, though, and wouldn't you know it, a certain zombie game-character-infested memory card was just put on sale!

At first Lucy hated Guy. Working at a farm in Australia, grinding flour, Guy constantly calls her "Cinderella." Whenever he does, she feels like smiling and has a hard time calming down. Guy is handsome and smells of the privileged classes, but then again, since he is a visitor to the farm it is easy to think this. And now, due to certain circumstances, she finds herself returning to London. It just so happens that Guy is also returning, and they are sitting beside each other on the flight. She would never have thought that only a couple days later she would be working at his company and referring to him as her boyfriend.
name: Bridegroom Boss II

description:
Lodger from Hell

Meet Aranya, and archdemon from hell! He quite enjoys his life, being one of Satan's right hands. But while Satan goes on vacation something weird happens and Aranya turns into the most wanted demon in hell! Scared, he decides to flee to the surface, also known as Earth. He meets the humans Sanna and Simon who are about to get their lives turned upside-down..!

Aranya is a comedic adventure with fantasy elements, set in a small town in Sweden. Inspired by shounen manga and various humorous comic books, you're in for a fun adventure!
name: Lodger From Hell

description: Thanatos, a lone conspiracy theorist, who believes one day the world will be overrun with zombies. He's trained his whole life for that day, even though most people view him as crazy. One day, while at work, his worst fears come true! Now he and an orphaned little girl, Dinah, must make it through a zombie ridden city and survive!

BAD KARMA VOLUME ONE is a 200 page hardcover comics, prose and art collection by Alex Grecian, Jeremy Haun, B. Clay Moore & Seth Peck and acclaimed collaborators, featuring five separate, inter-related creator-owned concepts.

Release Dates

  • Digital - June 18, 2014
  • Print - May 20, 2015
name: HC

description: All the issues combined into this Omnibus featuring Bluewater's pirate series. Fifteen men on a dead man's chest. But in this story, the men happen to be zombies, and they sail with the most blood thirsty female pirate on the Spanish Main. Hanna the pirate battles against unbeatable odds in her quest to find her notorious father Blackbeard. Featuring cover model Bayatch's Traci Bingham.
name: TPB

description:
Monkey See... Monkey Free?! Part One

The BlackGuard have just completed their first mission... and they COMPLETELY botched it! Now their leader, Mercer, has to piece together just how exactly things went so wrong.
name: Monkey See... Monkey Free?! Part One

description:
Collects BubbleGun #1-5!

They like the tech, but live for the high stakes! Sisters Molli and Devyn, along with teammates Roman and Kyo-and a stockpile of cutting edge, cyber-punk technology, form a confident team of mercenary thieves able to take on the most formidable jobs around. Yet, when one cyber heist turns out to be more than they bargained for, as a mysterious package and its contents threaten to unravel the group to its core, the menacing worlds of corrupt industry and deadly espionage is unleashed upon them! Now, enjoy all five issues of the epic first volume on one collection!
name: TPB

description:
A Tale of the Inferior

Lieutenant Lightning finds himself reeling with despair after recent tragic events, and seeks the counsel of his colleagues: The Enigmatic Gearman and The Marvelous Manticore. While sulking at Gearman's penthouse, Ll's desperation leads to revelations that will change their friendship forever...or at least until issue 2.
name: A Tale of the Inferior!

description:
Earthly Child (and Robot!)

Carl has built a time travelling helmet! Along with his best robot buddy Zip, he's going on a time travelling adventure to...somewhere?

Collecting comics 1-30 of Carl and Zip's Adventures Through Time!
name: Earthly Child (and Robot!)

volume.name: Carl and Zip's Adventures Through Time!

description: 2014 is Cavewoman's 20th anniversary! This very special item is our 2014 full-color Show Book! Inside you will find the original colored version of the 'boot story' from Jungle Tales #2. Budd did the original artwork in full color, but we printed it black and white. Besides Budd, only 2 or 3 people have ever seen the original colored artwork - until now! The rest of this special book is filled with brand new, never before seen Cavewoman color pinups. There is also a page to get a sketch if you can grab Budd at a show. Each book is signed by Budd, limited to just 1000 copies, and also bagged & boarded with a Certificate of Authenticity!
A true story about two adventurers unwittingly walking through a war zone on their way to the Amazon. It's told as all stories about martial law and drug cartels should be: in whimsical rhyme.

Natural Born Wanna-Bes

Set in the late 90s, Stickboy's trip home for the weekend turns upside down as he and his best bud Psychoboy deal with a world that's gone mad.
name: Natural Born Wanna-Bes

description: Nicky Trainor grew up in a working class South Boston neighborhood. In and out of trouble growing up, Nicky ran with a neighborhood gang who called themselves the Dead End Boys. After Nicky's cousin Mikey was shot and killed by a rival gang member, Nicky cleaned himself up and at the age of 22 joined the Boston Police Department.
name: TPB

description:
Bestselling cartoonist Jim Benton of It's Happy Bunny and Dear Dumb Diary fame has also been posting whimsical, dry humored, at times nasty, comics on Reddit. They have become one of the site's most popular items. At last, here is a collection all in one place! From wry observation of the absurdities of life to acerbic comment, to poetic musings, from cats and dogs to humans, from one size to another, one style to another, this compendium will amaze as to the breadth of Benton's inexhaustible talent for humor.

Note: The digital edition (6/18/2014) for this volume came out before the print edition.

volume.name: Dog Butts and Love. And Stuff Like That. And Cats.

description:
Prelude

The world of Hisren was almost destroyed by the Four Dragons. Using dark magic's, they took control of peoples minds and started a war that would last over a hundred years. They were only stopped by three gifted human brothers known as the Johnsons. After the war ended, the Johnsons were betrayed by their own allies and every one of them was killed, for they feared for having too much power.

It's been nine years since the Johnson tragedy. Jakean Wuthers, a young sword-smith, must defend his home and loved ones when bandits arrive lead by a powerful monster arrive and take control. Jakean must be careful however, because he carries a secret. A secret that the bandit leader soon discovers...
name: Prelude

description: FARSCAPE CONTINUES! The ultimate collection FARSCAPE fans have been waiting for! This handsome hardcover features the first four issues of the first arc of the Farscape comic series as written by series creator Rockne S. O’Bannon. Includes a bevy of bonus materials that make this a must-have item for hard-core ‘Scapers and new fans alike!
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Farscape: The Beginning of the End of the Beginning

description: Zhaan and D’Argo are alive! Crichton’s not married to Aeryn anymore! What’s going on? Crichton has found himself in an alternate timeline. His friends are alive, but his wife is still part of the Peacekeepers. Can he get back? Will he ever see Aeryn again? From series creator Rockne S. O’Bannon and writer Keith R.A. DeCandido!
name: Volume 3

description: Pilot’s home planet is under attack! The crew of Moya gets a close-up look at the world that birthed their trusted navigator. But Moya is not the only ship that has come to help. Aeryn gets a shocker when she sees who else is in their corner. Another red hot collection of the new ongoing FARSCAPE series written by the show creator Rockne S. O’Bannon!
name: Volume 5

description: A conspiracy threatens the end of the Uncharted Territories and not one, but two Leviathan crews - the outlaws on Maya and a new crew of ex-Peacekeepers - team up to take on the conspiracy! And the result will certainly blow your mind! It's the Farscape event you can't miss, as series creator Rockne S. O'Bannon grabs "The War for the Uncharted Territories" and turns it up to eleven!
name: Volume 6

description:
Issue 1 opens with a "BANG!" as we see the world surrounding

Father Pedro. Bored, restless, disillusioned and trying to temper his growing impatience, he tries to do right by his congregation while all around him he sees humanity eating each other alive. When a recurring dream seems to cross over into actual existence, Father 'Pete' must confront his eroding commitment to the church and his faith.
name: Faith

description:
The Dawn of Man

The story of first men and the moment of our transformation to something more than beasts.
name: The Dawn of Man

description:
The Grimm Reaper Fiesta!

Grimm Reaper Fiesta Time! Grimm Reaper and Friends are in the mood for a vacation! What better way to party than travel to MEXICO for the Day of the Dead Celebration! In this issue, we meet Zombie Butler Roy's cousin Ray and Grimm new "Nephew" Grimmiss! AW YEAH first appearances! Stay away from Grimm's "death touch" or your party will come to a quick end! Presented DIGITALLY here for the first time as it was originally released in 2005! By Art Baltazar and Franco!

Get Ready to Get Killed

Get ready for thirty-six pages of explosive radness as you follow Gunwolf, Hirohito Co.'s number one reluctant corporate enforcer who has a penchant for synth-rock, a reputation for mayhem, and the skill set to carry it out. Sent on a mission to Orange Co., California, Gunwolf must lay waste to anyone that gets in his way in the sunny suburban wasteland or face reprogramming by Hirohito Co.'s elite force of Panda Women.
name: Get Ready to Get Killed

description: Meet Michael Finch, a two-time loser and expectant father, who is discovering that going legit is tough with a life long rap sheet. Luckily for Finch, there's an outfit in town handing out gigs to goons-- health benefits included! It's exactly what he needs, but Finch quickly discovers there is much more to being a Henchman than taking punches from a cape...
Human Stuff is a comic strip collection about the day to day moments in the life of Nacho Nova, a cartoonist returning to his hometown of El Paso, TX.

A Wolf... In Snake's Clothing

The Jack of Spades takes on a new kind of job... A rescue mission! As the media rages about the growing threat of the parahuman population, the Nuevas Vegas police force begin taking new precautions. Where does Spade fit in with the mounting politics? Who is his mysterious new client? And how are all these people just pawns for Caesar Serpent's plans?
name: A Wolf... In Snake's Clothing

description:
In a villa in London, England, there is a butler. An Adonis in looks and actions, his conduct is especially elegant and refined. His name is Yukihiko Sagara. As a butler, he must devote his loyalty to, and kneel at, his master’s feet. One day, a rather haughty guest appeared. He told Yuki that after feeling the sensation of his lips, he wanted him. Master and Butler. The servant and served. Will their positions change….? What type of butler would you desire?

Chapter Titles

  • The Kneeling Butler I
  • The Kneeling Butler II
  • The Kneeling Butler III
  • The Butler's Love Scheme First Part
  • The Butler's Love Scheme Last Part
  • The Butler Embraces the Doctor's Robe
name: Vol. 1

description: Her little brother, Steven, has disappeared with a million euros in tow? Gracie, seeking a more detailed explanation of what happened, rushes to the company where her brother works. The president of the company, Rocco De Marco, meets with her to explain that her brother has stolen money from them and disappeared. Furthermore, they are also questioning her as if she is an accomplice to the crime. "You are an important person in relation to the incident. Until Steven appears, we would like you to stay in the company penthouse on the top floor of the building." Isn't this imprisonment?
name: Vol. 1

description:
The Gentle Art of Making Enemies

McBlack reluctantly agrees to help a Killer Dame find her no-good husband, but soon he's up to his eyesockets in paramilitary cannibals and mutant cyborg bikers.

Perhaps this case is gonna be fun, after all...
name: The Gentle Art of Making Enemies

description:
The Most Remarkable Human Being Ever to Draw the Breath of Life.

Betrayed, robbed and left for dead by his tour manager, Merrick finds his way back to London where he is rediscovered by Dr. Frederick Treves who, unknown to Merrick, is the man responsible for his exile to Europe. Treves takes Merrick back to the London hospital where he can recover, promising to search for a cure to Merrick's condition but actually attempting to unlock the secret of his skin for his own gain.

MOTHER Knows Best

The day has come, Sylvia's wedding has arrived. But what wedding would be complete without the MOTHER of the bride.
name: MOTHER Knows Best

description: Six silent episodes. With only the sound of thought...

The A.B.C.s of Thievery

Our young search and rescue team are called into action on a violent and dangerous planet when one of their own goes missing and a device with power of great magnitude is stolen from their HQ.
name: The A.B.C.s of Thievery

volume.name: THE NANOC.A.M.P. (Cosmic Adventure of Maximum Potential)

description:
What happens to an artist, when some unwanted visitors decide to move into her head ?

In [No More] Ghosts, Valium, is struggling to explain, what happened to her, when a serious art block/depression, hit her hard.

Absolon Danard is an immortal troubleshooter in the employ of several nameless agencies across the world. He is quietly retired, living a simple life on a chicken farm when he gets called back into the game because his archenemy, the supernatural assassin called Taran Tu, has re-appeared, and is looking to ignite a global war by resurrecting the monstrous King of the Faeries and crushing mankind under his heel. Danard enters into a high stakes game of cat and mouse with the knowledge that if he fails...humanity will fall.
PANELS, Volume 1, is a playground of ideas where anything can happen, from mysterious beings crashing to earth, a bloody battle for a homeless kingdom, to a teleporting criminal.
name: Volume One

description:
With the re-imagining of an all-time classic, fans of the new and old will be immersed in the action, oppression and humanity in these untold RoboCop stories. Explore the world of the new film, brought to you by some of the freshest voices in the industry: Joe Harris (GREAT PACIFIC), Frank J. Barbiere (FIVE GHOSTS), Ed Brisson (SHELTERED), and Michael Moreci (HOAX HUNTERS), with art by Piotr Kowalski (MARVEL KNIGHTS: HULK), João Viera (TEENAGE MUTANT NINJA TURTLES), Jason Copland (DAREDEVIL), and Emilio Laiso (3 GUNS).

Collects the following one-shots:
Robocop: Beta
Robocop: Memento Mori
Robocop: To Live and Die in Detroit
Robocop: Hominem Ex Machina

Note: The digital edition (6/18/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: TPB

description:
Mars Gambit

3042 AD. The biggest military provider in the universe, Friendly Corp, is wiping out human colonies and claiming their land. This news never reaches the general alien and human public, keeping them unaware of the growing menace.

But a single teenage girl, Sage, has survived one of the massacres.

One survivor. One hope. One mission. She aims to bring down Friendly Corp. To win the war, Sage needs to expose the cover up. This leads her to the floating Cray City on Mars.

Friendly Corp has sent two bounty hunters after Sage, but she has a few cybernetic tricks up her sleeve - and Sage is not quite human anymore!
name: Mars Gambit

description:
Wars End

Explore the life of Jara as she finds something that will change her life forever!
name: Wars End

description:
Work for the Weary: Deluxe G-Mecha edition

Our story takes place on the streets of Oxenvale and follows Manolo "Nolo" Cienfuegos, a tough, ambitious teenager who is building a surprisingly lucrative snow shoveling empire with his crew. As his empire expands he wrestles with the success and stress that come with it, along with school, homework, girls, family responsibility and everything else a teen faces. This deluxe edition contains the bonus story, G-Mechadon Alpha Zegas.

When a teenage boy tries to wash away the evidence of his "solo activities," he ends up with a shocking surprise that is much harder to hide. The slightly perverse meets the surprisingly sweet in Part One of this hilarious coming-of-age tale.
Ullysses also known as SPECTRUM now having immense new powers must learn how to use them wisely while determining whom he should help and battle

The Apocalypse Party Part One

There's something lurking in the woods deep in the South Wales Valleys.

Don, a fed up call center worker, and his talking monkey buddy-pal, Kenny McMonkey, have a secret: they are zombie hunters!

When a regular hunt gets weirder than usual, the monkey poop hits the fan.

Can our heroes make it out alive? And what do his mates think he's up to? And how exactly does a monkey drink a bottle of whiskey?
name: The Apocalypse Party Part One

description: This is a collection of the first five issues of TenState by Tom Merritt and Len Peralta. Includes a BleedingCool.com interview with the creators plus a gallery of sketches and cover art concepts.
name: Vol. 1

description: Introduction by Bill Maher. The world's first "Instant Graphic Novel!" When U.S. bombs started raining on the Taliban, Rall didn't just watch it on TV - he jumped on a plane straight to the war zone to get the real story for himself. But the only cartoonist to go to Afghanistan got more than he bargained for, way more than his previous gut-wrenching trip deep up the legendary Silk Road. Within days of arriving, armed men were hunting down journalists to murder and rob them. Waving funnies didn't help. From the gruesome spectacle of a Taliban prisoner blowing himself up with grenades to the hilarious image of mujahideen lining up for shaves and DVD porn a day after joining the Northern Alliance, you can count on Rall for a decidedly different take on this gritty war. To Afghanistan and Back features as its centerpiece a 50-page graphic novel travelogue of his experience as a cartoonist and war correspondent. It also includes Rall's articles, cartoons and photos as filed from the front for the Village Voice and syndicated throughout America.
name: GN

description:
Flowers In The Window

The Leon drug cartel is one step away from controlling the border area between the US and Mexico. His secret weapon: viciously skilled assassins that he raised as his own daughters.
name: Flowers In The Window

description:
Thicker than water

It's the early 18th century and a crazed sole-survivor insists that there were demonic forces at work when his vessel was overrun by villainous monsters. Dare we say... Vampire Pirates? Young Ian must travel the high seas to find his lost brother -- and battle his darkest fears. Eisner nominated comic artist Jeromy Cox teams with Kevin Ring to bring you swash buckling action seasoned with a dash of horror and a pinch of romance. Okay, maybe we slipped a few extra dashes of horror in there.
name: Part One: Thicker Than Water

description: In the country of Thomas Isle lives princess Louisa, whom the people referred to as Snow White, for she has been sheltered her entire life by overprotective family members. Even now at 27 she's still innocent. At a ball one evening, she encounters a charming man named Garrett. He's the most prominent and affluent industrialist in the country. As if in a fairy-tale love story from her dreams, when she sees Garrett she feels like destiny is calling. Garrett also does little to conceal his affection for the princess. The overly pure princess's love doesn't look before it leaps. She would never in her wildest dreams have thought that this meeting was a part of some diabolical scheme...
name: Vol. 1

description: Five complete stories of highbrow tactics, military minutiae, battlefield dissonance and (thankfully) unrelenting action! Following a heedless cast of commonplace soldiers, "A Wary Distance" brings an irreverent modern sensibility to warfare, raging from dusty plain to open trench, ruined city to the farthest reaches of outer space.

Woodland Welfare manifesto is the story of Burnt Bear, Crazy Rabbit, and Perverted Monkey-3 proletarian animals who struggle against corrupt capitalist system that oppresses forest with iron fist of injustice! Will trio of friends triumph when working-class livelihoods are threatened, or will Crazy Rabbit's anarchist methods Threaten to make them all enemies of the state?

A prequel story to the award-winning, critically acclaimed horror feature film Zombie Dawn. A zombie outbreak has trapped a family 'behind enemy lines' with little hope to get out of the quarantine zone. But somehow they must make their way to the safe zone before the border is sealed permanently. Or decide to stay within the zombie infested zone and leave their fate up to God.

volume.name: Casey Ruggles: King of the Horsemen
